DESIGNING
TUNNEL
DIODE
CIRCUITS
USING
COMPOSITE
CHARACTERISTICS
WITH
TUNNEL
DIODES
CONNECTED
IN
SERIES
CERTAIN
RELATIONS
BETWEEN
THEIR
PEAK
AND
VALLEY
CURRENTS
AND
THEIR
FINAL
VOLTAGES
CAN
BE
SATISFIED
SO
THAT
THE
COMPOSITE
CURVE
HAS
PEAKS
VALLEYS
AND
STABLE
POSITIVE
REGIONS
THE
USE
OF
THIS
TYPE
OF
CHARACTERISTIC
FOR
BINARY
ADDITION
SCALING
